  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 6 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0b89\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "More than 6 million people are food insecure in Sri Lanka - World Food Program report",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "6.3 million people in Sri Lanka are food insecure. The World Food Program has warned that this situation will worsen as the crisis progresses.",
        "This has been mentioned in the report published by the World Food Program on the 15th regarding the food security situation in Sri Lanka.",
        "6.7 million people do not consume an acceptable diet. If farmers do not get access to seeds, fertilizer and financial support, rice yields are at risk of falling by as much as 50 percent in the coming monsoon. Also, the fisheries and animal husbandry sectors will face an irreversible situation.",
        "6.3 million people are food insecure nationally. It is 28.3 per cent. At least 65,600 of them are on severe food security. These figures are likely to increase drastically.",
        "Skyrocketing food costs make it difficult for people to meet their nutritional needs. About 6.7 million people do not eat enough food and 5.3 million people are reducing the number of foods they eat.",
        "In the last three months the income has decreased drastically. Two in five households report that their income has halved. 5 million people use crisis or emergency livelihood coping strategies to cope with food insecurity.",
        "It is noted that this may affect their medium- and long-term capacity for income-generating activities and food security."
      ],
